[[File:Harpie Bug Swarm icon.png|left]]
'''Harpie bug swarms''' are mid-level [[slayer monsters]] that require a [[Slayer]] level of 33 to kill. A [[lit bug lantern]], which requires a [[Firemaking]] level of 33 to light is required to damage these [[monsters]] (the lantern '''must''' be lit ''and'' equipped). If you do not have 33 Firemaking, you cannot be assigned harpie bug swarms as a [[Slayer task]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/914564835446284288|date=1 October 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.is/5J0ym|archivedate=25 May 2020|quote=I think all three of the checks you list are still in effect on the creatures in question. Reducing requirements tends not to be popular.}} 

Harpie bug swarms should be an easy task for well-equipped mid-level players; their abundance as well as the fact that they remain aggressive to players until level 93 combat makes this task very click-easy. As harpie bug swarms are ''very'' accurate, and will often hit for up to 6 [[hitpoints]], it is advisable to have [[Defence]] levels from 40-50+ and to bring [[food]] appropriate for the player's level, such as [[lobster]]s. Another option for those that have completed [[Tai Bwo Wannai Trio]] is to keep [[Protect from Melee]] up and recharge prayer at the [[Tribal Statue]] about 30 seconds away.

It is recommended to bring [[nature rune]]s while slaying this monster since it has many drops that can be [[High Level Alchemy|alched]] to free up [[inventory]] spaces, and [[fire rune]]s are frequently dropped from this monster.

There are two [[safespot]]s: one between the two trees to the south behind the small jungle plant, and another to the north on the beaches of the fairy ring (DKP). Players can setup a cannon to range or melee 2+ swarms to the west, but will need runes to [[telegrab]] any desired drops.

You can use a [[Dwarf multicannon|Dwarf Multicannon]] in this location, but you have to equip the bug lantern for the cannon to deal damage.

